# TopBar Component

When a Figma design includes a top bar (navigation bar at the top of the page), always use the existing `TopBar` component located at `src/components/TopBar.vue`. **Never** recreate a top bar from scratch.

## Import

```typescript
import TopBar from '@/components/TopBar.vue';
// or relative path
import TopBar from '../../components/TopBar.vue';
```

## Default Behavior

The TopBar renders out of the box with:
- **AI Search icon** (`AiSearchIcon` from `@jumpcloud/icons`)
- **Search placeholder**: `"Search User, Devices, Apps, etc..."`
- **Shortcut tag**: `"⌘/Ctrl + K"`
- **4 icon buttons** (Customer Support, Lifebuoy, Flag, Checklist)
- **AI Assistant gradient button** (`AiAgentButton` from Circuit DS)

```html
<!-- Simplest usage — all defaults -->
<TopBar />
```

## Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `searchPlaceholder` | `string` | `'Search User, Devices, Apps, etc...'` | Placeholder text in the search area |
| `shortcutLabel` | `string` | `'⌘/Ctrl + K'` | Keyboard shortcut shown as a Tag |
| `showSearchIcon` | `boolean` | `true` | Toggle the AI search icon |
| `iconButtons` | `TopBarIconButton[]` | 4 default buttons | Custom icon buttons on the right |

### TopBarIconButton interface

```typescript
interface TopBarIconButton {
  icon: Component;   // Vue component (Heroicon or JumpCloud icon)
  label: string;     // Accessible label / identifier
  onClick?: () => void;
}
```

## Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `search-click` | — | Search area clicked |
| `icon-button-click` | `label: string` | An icon button clicked |
| `ai-assistant-click` | `event: Event` | AI Assistant button clicked |

## Slots

| Slot | Description |
|---|---|
| `search-icon` | Replace the default AI search icon |
| `icon-buttons` | Replace all default icon buttons |

## Customizing Icon Buttons

```typescript
import { markRaw } from 'vue';
import { Cog6ToothIcon, BellIcon } from '@heroicons/vue/24/outline';

const myButtons = [
  { icon: markRaw(Cog6ToothIcon), label: 'Settings' },
  { icon: markRaw(BellIcon), label: 'Notifications' },
];
```

```html
<TopBar :iconButtons="myButtons" />
```

## Page Layout Integration

Place the TopBar as the first child inside the main content area, after `AppNavigation`:

```html
<div class="flex h-screen overflow-hidden">
  <AppNavigation ... />
  <div class="flex-1 flex flex-col min-w-0 overflow-auto">
    <TopBar />
    <!-- Page content below -->
  </div>
</div>
```

## Detection Rule

If a Figma design contains any of the following, use this component:
- A node named **"Top Bar"**, **"Top Bar / Bar"**, or **"TopBar"**
- A horizontal bar at `y=0` of the main content area with a search field and action buttons
- An **AI Assistant** gradient button on the right edge
- A search area with an AI search icon and keyboard shortcut tag
